        "content": "<p>Here is the discussion thread on the formalization of some basic concepts of Iwasawa Theory in Lean.</p>\n<p>It's a tentative project in Academy of Mathematics and Systems Science, Chinese Academy of Sciences.</p>\n<p>I've setup a basic WIP blueprint website at <a href=\"https://acmepjz.github.io/lean-iwasawa\">https://acmepjz.github.io/lean-iwasawa</a>.</p>\n<p>The first goal of this project is formalize the proof (to some extent as much as possible) of the following result of Iwasawa on growth of class groups in <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi><mi>p</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{Z}_p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.975em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>-extension.<br>\nDue to the funding period, this is expect to be concluded in the end of this year (2025).</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>Let <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>K</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span></span></span></span> be a number field, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span> be a prime, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>K</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">∞</mi></msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">/</mi><mi>K</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K_{\\infty}/K</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\"><span class=\"mord mtight\">∞</span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mord\">/</span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span></span></span></span> be a <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi><mi>p</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{Z}_p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.975em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>-extension.<br>\nThen there exists <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>λ</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>μ</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mi>ν</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\lambda,\\mu,\\nu</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8889em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">λ</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">μ</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.06366em;\">ν</span></span></span></span> such that for any sufficiently large <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">n</span></span></span></span>, <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">o</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">r</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">d</mi></mrow><mi>p</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mrow><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">C</mi><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">l</mi></mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>n</mi></msub><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>μ</mi><msup><mi>p</mi><mi>n</mi></msup><mo>+</mo><mi>λ</mi><mi>n</mi><mo>+</mo><mi>ν</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathrm{ord}_p(\\mathrm{Cl}(K_n))=\\mu p^n+\\lambda n+\\nu</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1.0361em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">ord</span></span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathrm\">Cl</span></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">))</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span><span class=\"mrel\">=</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2778em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8588em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">μ</span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.6644em;\"><span style=\"top:-3.063em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.7778em;vertical-align:-0.0833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">λn</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span><span class=\"mbin\">+</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.2222em;\"></span></span><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.4306em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.06366em;\">ν</span></span></span></span>.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>The proof of it requires certain amount of commutative algebra and algebraic number theory (more precisely, global class field theory).</p>\n<p>The next goal is a longer term goal, which is to formalize the proof of cyclotomic Iwasawa Main Conjecture which relates class groups of cyclotomic <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"double-struck\">Z</mi><mi>p</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\mathbb{Z}_p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.975em;vertical-align:-0.2861em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathbb\">Z</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">p</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.2861em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>-extensions to Kubota-Leopoldt <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>p</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">p</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.625em;vertical-align:-0.1944em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">p</span></span></span></span>-adic <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mi>L</mi></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">L</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.6833em;\"></span><span class=\"mord mathnormal\">L</span></span></span></span>-functions.</p>\n<p>In this thread I want to collect suggestions, opinions and feedbacks to the project, including but not limited to:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>Prerequisites of mathematics which may be used in this project, including those already in mathlib, or in PR, or in another repository, or in other ongoing projects. It's a bad idea to reinventing wheels.</li>\n<li>Suggestions for data structure designs.</li>\n<li>......</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Helps are welcome. Thanks in advance!</p>",
        "id": 510849171,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1744094020
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>If any students want to come to the Clay Math summer school on formalising class field theory, I would encourage them to apply! <a href=\"https://www.claymath.org/events/formalizing-class-field-theory/\">https://www.claymath.org/events/formalizing-class-field-theory/</a> Closing date for registrations is just a few weeks away.</p>",
        "id": 510849987,
        "sender_full_name": "Kevin Buzzard",
        "timestamp": 1744094381
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"110038\">Kevin Buzzard</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/116395-maths/topic/Discussion.20on.20formalization.20of.20Iwasawa.20Theory.20in.20Lean/near/510849987\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>If any students want to come to the Clay Math summer school on formalising class field theory, I would encourage them to apply!</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Thank you! I'll keep in mind if there are students interested in it.</p>\n<p>What I should do in our project is to keep the notation same as the formalizing class field theory project :).</p>",
        "id": 510850281,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1744094517
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"300245\">Filippo A. E. Nuccio</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/287929-mathlib4/topic/Abelian.20extension/near/510830739\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"366779\">Jz Pan</span> <a href=\"#narrow/stream/287929-mathlib4/topic/Abelian.20extension/near/510676824\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>BTW I'm trying <code>IsZpExtension</code> here <a href=\"https://github.com/acmepjz/lean-iwasawa/blob/master/Iwasawalib/FieldTheory/ZpExtension/Basic.lean\">https://github.com/acmepjz/lean-iwasawa/blob/master/Iwasawalib/FieldTheory/ZpExtension/Basic.lean</a> and I also defined a <code>CommGroup</code> instance. Clearly abelian extension is very useful in my application.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>BTW, although a bit unrelated to this, I think we really need to set up the theory of multiple Zp extensions from the start indexed by a Fintype <code>I</code> and have an <code>abbrev</code> for the special case <code>I=Unit</code> as we do for polynomials.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Yes, it's certainly useful for Rubin's work of Iwasawa theory on imaginary quadratic fields. But in several variable case I think it's not clear how to define <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">Γ</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">\\Gamma_n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord\">Γ</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:0em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> and <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K_n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span>.</p>",
        "id": 510850735,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1744094707
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>Not only Rubin's work, pretty much everything about modern (post 1970) Iwasawa theory needs to speak about multiple Zp extensions at a certain point: Leopoldt conjecture, maximal p-ramified extensions, Iwasawa th for elliptic curves and modular forms, etc. We can discuss things in Beijing in three weeks time, but if I have an idea about a nice definition for intermediate fields in between I'll mention it here. For the time being, I looked at your repo and I think all your preliminary results about uniqueness of subgrouos of given index and their topology will be useful, even in the rank-1 case.</p>",
        "id": 510854824,
        "sender_full_name": "Filippo A. E. Nuccio",
        "timestamp": 1744096242
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"300245\">Filippo A. E. Nuccio</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/116395-maths/topic/Discussion.20on.20formalization.20of.20Iwasawa.20Theory.20in.20Lean/near/510854824\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>We can discuss things in Beijing in three weeks time</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Sure.</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>but if I have an idea about a nice definition for intermediate fields in between I'll mention it here.</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Sure. My plan is currently just define <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><msub><mi>K</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">K_n</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:0.8333em;vertical-align:-0.15em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal\" style=\"margin-right:0.07153em;\">K</span><span class=\"msupsub\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1514em;\"><span style=\"top:-2.55em;margin-left:-0.0715em;margin-right:0.05em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:2.7em;\"></span><span class=\"sizing reset-size6 size3 mtight\"><span class=\"mord mathnormal mtight\">n</span></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.15em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span></span> for <code>[Unique I]</code> case, and only define the subfield for several variable case when there are applications.</p>",
        "id": 510856497,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1744096877
    },
    {
        "content": "<blockquote>\n<p>I think we really need to set up the theory of multiple Zp extensions from the start indexed by a Fintype <code>I</code> and have an <code>abbrev</code> for the special case <code>I=Unit</code></p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Now I defined <code>IsMvZpExtension</code> along with <code>IsZpExtension</code>. Since both of them are <code>Prop</code>s, if using Fintype <code>I</code> I still need a lemma that <code>IsMvZpExtension</code> depends on the cardinality of <code>I</code>. So I decide to make <code>IsMvZpExtension</code> accepts a natural number <code>d</code> as dimension for input, rather than a Fintype <code>I</code>. Hope it will not introduce troubles.</p>\n<p>Meanwhile maybe we need a <code>Type</code> <code>MvZpExtension</code> which carries the data <code>I</code> as well as a fixed isomorphism of Galois group to <code>Zp^d</code>. For example in imaginary quadratic setting, we may choose (cyclotomic,anticyclotomic) directions, or <span class=\"katex\"><span class=\"katex-mathml\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><semantics><mrow><mo stretchy=\"false\">(</mo><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">p</mi><mo separator=\"true\">,</mo><mover accent=\"true\"><mi mathvariant=\"fraktur\">p</mi><mo stretchy=\"true\">‾</mo></mover><mo stretchy=\"false\">)</mo></mrow><annotation encoding=\"application/x-tex\">(\\mathfrak{p},\\overline{\\mathfrak{p}})</annotation></semantics></math></span><span class=\"katex-html\" aria-hidden=\"true\"><span class=\"base\"><span class=\"strut\" style=\"height:1em;vertical-align:-0.25em;\"></span><span class=\"mopen\">(</span><span class=\"mord mathfrak\">p</span><span class=\"mpunct\">,</span><span class=\"mspace\" style=\"margin-right:0.1667em;\"></span><span class=\"mord overline\"><span class=\"vlist-t vlist-t2\"><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.724em;\"><span style=\"top:-3em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"mord\"><span class=\"mord mathfrak\">p</span></span></span><span style=\"top:-3.644em;\"><span class=\"pstrut\" style=\"height:3em;\"></span><span class=\"overline-line\" style=\"border-bottom-width:0.04em;\"></span></span></span><span class=\"vlist-s\">​</span></span><span class=\"vlist-r\"><span class=\"vlist\" style=\"height:0.1891em;\"><span></span></span></span></span></span><span class=\"mclose\">)</span></span></span></span> directions.</p>",
        "id": 511428150,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1744295620
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>I think that the structure <code>MvZpExtension</code> would be useful, indeed. I am not sure yet whether having a general <code>I</code> rather than a <code>Fin n</code> is a problem, but I am not sure about the problem here: if you only define <code>IsZpExtension</code> as the existence of an iso between the Galois group and <code>I -&gt; Zp</code>, can' you apply this def to <code>Fin d</code> when this makes your life easier?</p>",
        "id": 511800882,
        "sender_full_name": "Filippo A. E. Nuccio",
        "timestamp": 1744455681
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span class=\"user-mention silent\" data-user-id=\"300245\">Filippo A. E. Nuccio</span> <a href=\"#narrow/channel/116395-maths/topic/Discussion.20on.20formalization.20of.20Iwasawa.20Theory.20in.20Lean/near/511800882\">said</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I am not sure yet whether having a general <code>I</code> rather than a <code>Fin n</code> is a problem</p>\n</blockquote>\n<p>Suppose there are <code>I</code> and <code>J</code> with same cardinality. Then <code>IsMvZpExtension p I K L</code> if and only if <code>IsMvZpExtension p J K L</code>. But you need a lemma for this (although its proof is trivial).</p>\n<p>If I just use a number, then it just becomes <code>IsMvZpExtension p d K L</code> where <code>d = #I = #J</code>. (Here <code>#</code> means <code>Nat.card</code>.)<br>\nAnd <code>IsMvZpExtension p d K L = IsMvZpExtension p #I K L = IsMvZpExtension p #J K L</code> is just by <code>rw</code>.</p>\n<p>For the data version <code>MvZpExtension p I K L</code> it could have a lemma which implies <code>IsMvZpExtension p #I K L</code>.</p>",
        "id": 511809251,
        "sender_full_name": "Jz Pan",
        "timestamp": 1744462344
    },
